  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "「マイケル・ジャクソンズ ムーンウォーカー」は、マイケル・ジャクソンの映画を基にしたゲームです。ミスター・ビッグが子供たちを誘拐し、薬を盛ったり奴隷にしたりといった悪事を企んでいます。マイケルがその力を使って、彼の小さな友達を救うことが求められます。\n\nマイケル・ジャクソン（MJ）は、ジャンプしたり、魔法の星を投げたり、ダンスをして敵に立ち向かいながら、隠れた子供たちを探します。ステージは、MJのミュージックビデオの一部である街や墓地の形をしています。",
      "lang": "ja",
      "source": "romu"
    },
    {
      "text": "Several video games based on the 1988 Michael Jackson film Moonwalker. U.S. Gold published various games for home computers, released in 1989, whilst Sega developed two similarly themed beat 'em up video games in 1990; one released for arcades and another released for the Mega Drive/Genesis and Master System.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "igdb"
    },
    {
      "text": "\"Michael!\" Katy's voice rings out - you've found her! But more children are still lost! Can you stop the psycho mastermind Mr. Big and his goon squad before they kidnap all the kids? You can, if you're Michael Jackson! Moonwalk on muggers, lean on meanies, and pop the punks! Outfight, outjump, outdance! Move like only Michael can, to the beat of Smooth Criminal, Beat it, Billie Jean, and Bad! No bad guy can last through Michael's Star Magic! Punch down gangsters in Club 30. Rumble in the streets. Swing, spin, and kick past graveyard ghouls. Chill in the caverns, then sizzle 'em with ultra-tech weapons in Mr. Big's hideout. Experience the baddest video game ever. Defy physics with Michael's dancing! You never lose your cool. See it and be it - Michael Jackson's Moonwalker!",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "igdb_storyline"
    },
